# Gemini Vision Service for Viam

A lightweight Viam **Vision Service** that turns any Viam‑managed camera into a
“describe what you see” endpoint powered by Google Gemini.  
For every frame requested through `CaptureAllFromCamera`, the module sends the
image to Gemini 2.0 Flash and returns the model’s one‑sentence caption as a
Viam `Classification`.

## Features
- **Zero‑setup image captioning** – no local model weights; relies on
  Google Generative AI.
- **Drop‑in Vision Service** – looks like any other Viam component; works with
  Data Manager, `do_command`, etc.
- **Async friendly** – Gemini calls use the SDK’s aio client so the module
  never blocks Viam’s event loop.
- **Minimal dependencies** – `google‑genai`, `pillow`, `viam‑sdk==0.*`.

---

## Example Attributes Guide



      "attributes": {
        "api_key": "YOUR_GEMINI_API_KEY",
        "camera_name": "front-door-cam"
      }

## Example Call
vision = robot.get_service("Vision", name="myGeminiVision")
result  = await vision.capture_all_from_camera("front-door-cam",
                                               return_image=False,
                                               return_classifications=True)
print(result.classifications[0].class_name)

Attribute | Type | Required | Description
api_key | string | yes | Google Gemini API key.
camera_name | string | yes | Name of the Viam camera to pull frames from.
model_id | string | no | Override model (default gemini-2.0-flash).